==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Utilitarianism
<hw>U*til`i*ta"ri*an*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The doctrine that the greatest happiness of the greatest number
should be the end and aim of all social and political
institutions.</def> <rj><au>Bentham.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The doctrine that virtue is founded in utility, or
that virtue is defined and enforced by its tendency to promote the
highest happiness of the universe.</def> <rj><au>J. S.
Mill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The doctrine that utility is the sole standard of
morality, so that the rectitude of an action is determined by its
usefulness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Utility</ent>⟦br⟧
